            <bug_when>2009-10-21 13:25:38 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>On a fatal exception, the generator terminates printing the Python stack trace, 
together with the error message. This confuses people and obscures the error 
message, as the stack trace might be long and full of internal details. Make 
this optional, so it can be switched on on demand, as it is an important aid 
for error tracking.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>13390</commentid>
            <who name="Thomas Herchenroeder">thron7</who>
            <bug_when>2009-10-21 13:40:47 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Add a -s/--stacktrace CL option to the generator, to turn on printing of stack 
traces on fatal exits. The printing is off by default.

With r20441.</thetext>
